<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-09-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-09-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="204" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                        <head>204. Telegram 744 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d204fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files,
                                611.93/9–2055. Official Use Only; Niact.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-09-20">September 20, 1955, 3
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d204-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d204-1"/>
                        <p>744. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                        <p>In reply press inquiries am informing them for background that agreed
                            statement following today’s meeting should not be interpreted as
                            representing any change in US position set forth my September 14
                            statement. Today’s statement merely expresses what is already public
                            knowledge, that is there is difference of view between <persName corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName> and myself on timing discussion
                            item two of agenda.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName><hi rend="strong">Shillock</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>